<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-36-0961 </DOCNO><TEXT>Computed tomography and echography have proved to be more valuable thanarteriography for radiological spleen investigation. The ultrasonic andcomputed tomographic appearance of the spleen in normal and pathologicalstates is presented. Computed tomography is characterized by a lack ofsensitivity and specificity for lymphoma diagnosis.</TEXT></DOC>